        <mxCell id="INSTR" parent="1" style="text;html=1;fontSize=13;align=left;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;rounded=1;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=10;" value="&lt;b&gt;HOW TO JOIN WITH METRO ER DIAGRAM:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt; 1. Copy this entire diagram (Ctrl+A → Ctrl+C)&lt;br&gt; 2. Open metro ER diagram in draw.io&lt;br&gt; 3. Paste (Ctrl+V) — it adds to same canvas&lt;br&gt; 4. Move bus diagram to the right of metro diagram&lt;br&gt; 5. DELETE the two red &#39;External Reference&#39; boxes&lt;br&gt;    (metro.STATION and metro.PASSENGER)&lt;br&gt; 6. Draw lines to the ACTUAL metro entities:&lt;br&gt;    • INTERCHANGE_POINT.metro_station_id → metro.STATION&lt;br&gt;    • BUS_TICKET.passenger_id → metro.PASSENGER&lt;br&gt;    • BUS_TRAVEL_PASS.passenger_id → metro.PASSENGER&lt;br&gt;    • BUS_TRAVELLING_IN.passenger_id → metro.PASSENGER&lt;br&gt;    • BUS_FEEDBACK.passenger_id → metro.PASSENGER&lt;br&gt;    • COMBINED_JOURNEY.passenger_id → metro.PASSENGER&lt;br&gt; 7. That&#39;s it — full integrated ER is ready!" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="650" x="-350" y="750" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
